The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 28: The core sector grew 5.1 per cent in April, boosting prospects of an overall healthy industrial growth for the month. The six key industries crude, coal, petroleum refinery products, electricity, cement and finished steel  had grown 7.2 per cent in March and 3.7 per cent in April 2009.                             
	 Mumbai, May 28: Kingfisher Airlines has narrowed its net loss for the year ended March 31 by Rs 493 crore to Rs 1,647 crore from Rs 2,139.65 crore a year ago. Income from operations was down marginally at Rs 5,068 crore against Rs 5,239 crore a year ago.                             
	 New Delhi, May 28: The government has set up an advisory council to monitor safety issues and advise new rules for airports and airlines. The council, which will comprise 28 experts, will recommend the best regulatory practices to the director-general of civil aviation.                             
	 Calcutta, May 28: SsangYong Motor has received seven bids for the proposed majority stake sale of the company. The bidders include Pawan Kumar Ruia, Mahindra amp; Mahindra, Young An Hat Co, SM Aluminum and Seoul Investments.                             
	 Mumbai, May 28: Bank of Rajasthan (BoR) has suffered a net loss of Rs 102.13 crore in 2009-10 against a profit of Rs 117.71 crore last year.                                                                                                                          
